  "text": "Definition 2 (Weiermann [CITATION_1] ). On the interval [α, α + ω) the relations < n agree with <. If i < j then α + i < n α + j. Note, that α < m β implies α < n β for all n with m ≤ n. Moreover, the usual operations on ordinals are monotonic with respect to the relations < n .",
